Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the control flow of the Benchmark AI (BAI) system based on the provided repository summary:

```plantuml
@startuml awslabs_benchmark-ai

participant "User" as user
participant "bai-bff" as bff
participant "Kafka" as kafka
participant "executor" as executor
participant "watcher" as watcher
participant "fetcher-dispatcher" as fetcher
participant "Kubernetes" as k8s
participant "metrics-pusher" as metrics
participant "cloudwatch-exporter" as cw

user -> bff: Submit benchmark job
activate bff
bff -> bff: Validate TOML descriptor
bff -> kafka: Publish job submission event
deactivate bff

kafka -> executor: Consume job submission event
activate executor
executor -> executor: Translate descriptor to K8s resources
executor -> k8s: Create job resources
executor -> kafka: Publish job created event
deactivate executor

kafka -> watcher: Consume job created event
activate watcher
watcher -> k8s: Monitor job status
watcher -> kafka: Publish status updates
deactivate watcher

kafka -> fetcher: Consume job created event
activate fetcher
fetcher -> k8s: Create fetcher job
fetcher -> kafka: Publish data fetched event
deactivate fetcher

kafka -> executor: Consume data fetched event
activate executor
executor -> k8s: Update job with data location
deactivate executor

k8s -> metrics: Start metrics collection
activate metrics
metrics -> kafka: Push metrics
deactivate metrics

kafka -> cw: Consume metrics
activate cw
cw -> cw: Export metrics to CloudWatch
deactivate cw

watcher -> kafka: Publish job completed event
kafka -> bff: Consume job completed event
activate bff
bff -> user: Return job results
deactivate bff

@enduml
```